<item>
            <title>[HBASE-15877] user_permission does not list the permissions from namespace the table belongs to</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15877</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Re-create:&lt;br/&gt;
1. Get into hbase shell&lt;br/&gt;
2. create_namespace &apos;ns1&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
3. grant &apos;u1&apos;, &apos;RWX&apos;, &apos;@ns1&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
4. create &apos;ns1:t1&apos;, &apos;cf11&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
5. grant &apos;u2&apos;, &apos;RC&apos;, &apos;ns1:t1&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
6. user_permission &apos;ns1:t1&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The output of user_permission only lists u2&lt;br/&gt;
---------------------------&lt;br/&gt;
hbase(main):010:0* user_permission &apos;ns1:t1&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
User                          Namespace,Table,Family,Qualifier:Permission                                        &lt;br/&gt;
 u2                           ns1,ns1:t1,,: &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Permission: actions=READ,CREATE&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;                                               &lt;br/&gt;
---------------------------&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;u1 should be listed because t1 belongs to ns1, and u1 has the permissions to access ns1&lt;/p&gt;</description>
